data.output: It was my first day of secondary school and after much deliberation on my school outfit I decided on wearing my vintage Diesel jacket. I wanted to give off a cool and edgy look, and reinvent myself for the first day of big school. After checking over my rusty bicycle I realised a had a flat wheel so I used my dads old bike pump to give my wheels a boost! The last thing I wanted was a flat tyre on my first day. I wish my dad could have gave me a lift in, but his petrol car was so battered I would be so embarrassed to turn up in it, I opted for my bicycle.

I can't believe he just broke up with me, and even worse he broke up with me over text! My phone pinged and all I saw was the letter for his initials pop up on my text screen. Not even a curtsy call or anything, he simply wrote "This isn't working, it's over" and hit send. I shouldn't have expected anything more as he certainly doesn't get the stamp of approval from my parents.

I am the nerdy girl in school, the one who loves music not fashion or sports. My version of fun is learning a new instrument like the organ, not going shopping and spending loads of money! I guess I don't comply to the rest of the school social norms, I feel that in this world their empire is a complete different class compared to mine, I am boring and dull in comparison.

The gloom of tomorrow was chasing me as I had an incredibly important exam. I felt bad because if I received a bad grade I know my parents would kill me, if I failed their payment to me would be a year of misery locked in my room and forced to study. It would be like I didn't even exist to them, just another failed child who couldn't pass a maths exam.
